
=================
= Description: =
=================

This program reorders a given English text alphabetically according to the English version of the Hebrew alphabet. It takes a single argument, a string representing the text to be reordered, it removes all punctuation marks from the text before sorting it and returns the reordered text as a string.


=================
= Requirements: =
=================

Python 3.6 or later


==========
= Usage: =
==========

This program can be run from the command line using the following format:
 
python reorder_text.py <text_input> 

Replace <text_input> with the English text that you want to reorder. The output will be the reordered text as a string. Note that all punctuation marks will be removed from the text before sorting it.


============
= EXAMPLE: =
============

Suppose you want to reorder the following text: "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua"

From the command line, you would run the following command:

python reorder_text.py "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit, sed do eiusmod tempor incididunt ut labore et dolore magna aliqua"

The output of the program will be:

"adipiscing aliqua amet do dolor dolore tempor labore Lorem magna sit sed incididunt ipsum ut consectetur et elit eiusmod"

If you input a non-English text or invalid input, you will get an error message.
